Add this to .claude/settings.json:
  {                                                                                                                                                              
    "sandbox": {                                                                                                                                               
      "enabled": true,
      "filesystem": {
        "allowRead": ["."],
        "denyRead": ["~/"],
        "allowWrite": ["."],
        "denyWrite": ["/"]
      }                                                                                                                                                          
    }
  }

You can change the read part if you're ok with it reading outside. This feature was only added 10 days ago fwiw but it's great and pretty much this.

Seriously impressive, especially the viewport culling trick, not seen that one before.
FYI if you want to use inspect element, the viewport div consumes mouse elements, you can get rid of this with
  #viewport {
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  #viewport * {
    pointer-events: initial;
  }
